  "title": "10x Chromium Single Cell 5\u2032 Gene Expression v1.1",
  "description": "A droplet-based single-cell 5\u2032 gene-expression assay. Cells are partitioned into GEMs with barcoded gel beads; polyadenylated mRNA is reverse-transcribed with a poly(dT) RT primer and the reverse transcriptase template-switches onto the gel-bead oligo, placing a 16 nt 10x cell barcode and 10 nt UMI at the 5\u2032 end of each transcript. Amplified full-length cDNA is fragmented and built into a standard Illumina paired-end library. Read 1 (26 cyc) reads the 16 bp barcode + 10 bp UMI, the i7 read (8 cyc) reads the sample index, and Read 2 (91 cyc) reads the 5\u2032 cDNA insert.",
  "reference": {
    "kind": "protocol_doc",
    "label": "10x chromium 5 gene expression v1 1",
    "path": null,
    "url": null,
    "doi": null
  },
